stylometry: Sensitivity anaylsis allows us to change certain variables in order to view different outcomes of a given equation. It can help predict what a company may do if a given variable were to change. For instance lets say a company business is to ship oil. Sensitivity analysis will be able to change the cost to ship oil either reducing it or increasing it, and we will be able to determine what will be the cheapest route or path to ship the oil. SolverTable is the function or formula that makes sensitivity analysis possible. It is the function addon that is capable of changing specific variables in order to change the end result. It can help minimize a company's costs or maximize their profits, it can also serve to help answer other questions, such as the optimal solution for a set covering model as well.
